/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 644.0 Tm (When lightning strikes loose sand it can fuse a slender tube of glass called a fulgurite.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 630.0 Tm (Excavating and reconstructing forty fulgurites from a dune field, we relate their branching) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 616.0 Tm (morphology to the grain size and moisture of the host sand and estimate the extraordinarily) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 602.0 Tm (brief interval over which they form. We show that fulgurite shape preserves a readable) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 588.0 Tm (record of the current path of a single lightning discharge through the ground.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 574.0 Tm () Tj
