1 0 0 1 56 240.0 Tm (Fulgurite shape proved tightly linked to the sand it formed in. Coarse, dry sand produced) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 226.0 Tm (wide tubes with thick, rough walls, while finer sand yielded slender, smooth-walled tubes) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 212.0 Tm (that branched more freely. Moisture, by conducting current away from the main channel,) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 198.0 Tm (encouraged branching as the discharge sought multiple paths to ground.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 184.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 170.0 Tm (The branching itself is a faithful map of the current's descent. Each fork marks a point) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 156.0 Tm (where the discharge divided, and the relative diameters of the branches record how the) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 142.0 Tm (current split between them. A fulgurite is thus not a random glass tangle but a frozen) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 128.0 Tm (circuit diagram.) Tj
